      'Fascia damage often goes unnoticed because these boards are located at the roof edge where they are not easily visible from ground level. By the time you notice peeling paint, sagging gutters, or visible rot, the damage may have extended into the roof sheathing and rafter tails behind the fascia. Our proactive approach includes fascia inspection as part of every roof assessment we perform, catching deterioration early when repair is simple and affordable rather than waiting until replacement and structural repair are necessary. The relationship between fascia condition and gutter performance is direct and critical: when fascia boards soften or warp from moisture damage, the gutter hangers lose their grip and the entire gutter system begins to sag, overflow, and eventually pull away from the building.'
